Seventeen Chinese poachers were caught with 240 protected turtles, mostly dead, off Sabah's coast.
A group of 13 fishermen from Hainan were jailed for poaching nearly 80 turtles.
Despite the arrests, more poachers are expected due to the lucrative turtle trade.
Endangered sea turtles have been found dead along Bangladesh's coast, possibly due to pollution and fishing practices.
Conservation efforts are crucial as the Arakan forest turtle faces extinction.
Captive breeding programs serve as insurance policies to protect these critically endangered species.
The disappearance of turtles could disrupt the ecosystem, impacting marine life.
